HEADWORD: Disenthrall
<hw>Dis`en*thrall"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Enthrall</er>.]</ety> <def>To release from thralldom or slavery; to
give freedom to; to disinthrall.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>disenthral</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

